00:52:21,410 --> 00:52:24,710
PATTON: Captain Richard N. Jenson was a fine boy.

410
00:52:25,210 --> 00:52:28,810
Loyal, unselfish and efficient.

411
00:52:32,010 --> 00:52:34,210
I am terribly sorry.

412
00:52:43,410 --> 00:52:46,710
There are no coffins here since there is no wood.

413
00:52:47,610 --> 00:52:50,510
We will have a trumpeter and an honor guard...

414
00:52:50,710 --> 00:52:55,110
...but we will not fire the volleys as people would think an air raid was on.

415
00:53:11,310 --> 00:53:15,710
I enclosed a lock of Dick's hair in a letter to his mother.

416
00:53:17,910 --> 00:53:19,510
He was a fine man...

417
00:53:20,310 --> 00:53:21,810
...and a fine officer.

418
00:53:22,610 --> 00:53:24,910
And he had no vices.

419
00:53:33,610 --> 00:53:35,510
I shall miss him a lot.

420
00:53:45,710 --> 00:53:49,910
I can 't see the reason such fine young men get killed.

421
00:53:51,310 --> 00:53:54,110
